<br>
You would likely need to be in a high-performance guild to get the armor drops in ToV, but that's another matter entirely. Those items aren't tradeable; if they were, you'd see a fair amount of trading action with them as well (there is a decent amount of MQ offers as it is, given that some pieces drop enough that there are a few extras once everyone on the raid has their bits and pieces).<br>
<br>
All of this stuff is tradeable. The final armor quality is give-or-take planar level. An uber guild isn't going to be interested in it. Just keep a sharp eye out for your auction zones, and the Bazaar when it's up and running. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucicelygoldenfair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cicely goldenfair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#333333>(12/25/01 1:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=846.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The new mage armor (epic armor?)</span><hr size=1> from all i have heard/read... the twilight armor is going to be on par with hate/fear armor.  i know the monk legs were completed, i believe those stats are around ac10 str4 sta3 hp25 or so.  definitely not close to velious armor by any stretch of the imagination...<br>
